The '''XP-36 landspeeder''' was a [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlift]] vehicle, similar to a series of [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeder]] designs produced by [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub]]. It was a lightly armed, high performance speeder.<ref name="Epic">''[[The Epic Continues]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:85LineExt25XP36.jpg|thumb|250px|Prototype from Kenner's presentation binder]]
The XP-36 is only known to have existed as an unproduced toy prototype that was designed for the [[Kenner Products|Kenner]] toy line in the mid-1980s.<ref name="Prototype">{{WebCite|url=http://theswca.com/index.php?action=disp_item&item_id=50983|text=1985-86 Line Extension Presentation Binder Page 25 - XP-36 Landspeeder|work=The Star Wars Collectors Archive|archivedate=20161118020527}}</ref> The name was obviously intended as a reference to the XP-38 mentioned in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], and, was intended to be part of ''[[The Epic Continues]]'' toy line.<ref name="Tales">{{GalaxyCite|2|Galactic Bazaar|Galactic Bazaar: Tales of Phantom Toys}}</ref>

